===Mystery Realms===
A random player's realm defense must be challenged to receive the rewards. Only one attempt is allowed to challenge the realm. Rewards are also given regardless of a win or loss.

===Mystery Missions ===
Slips of paper appear and a mission must be done to receive the rewards. Missions can be any one of the following:

*Clear a Soul Zone 3 times.
*Clear an Explore Zone 1 time.
* Summon 1 time with a Mystery/Jade/AR Amulet.
*Do Demon Parade 1 time.

==Shared Events ==
Shared events are team Assembly Bosses that requires the collaboration of many players. There are 2 types of Assembly Bosses: Shikigami Bosses and Rare Boss. Assembly Bosses will be shared on the map for players nearby to challenge. Players can also invite friends or Guildmates that are not nearby to join. 

Players can see the battle against an Assembly Boss unfold and fight alongside other players. Each player can challenge up to 1 Rare Boss and up to 1 Shikigami Boss per day. Challenging a boss that players discovered themselves does not consume a daily attempt. Defeated players can continue to challenge the same Assembly Boss, but must wait 60 seconds before challenging them again. Players can chat with other players fighting the same Assembly Boss in the Team chat channel.
=== Shikigami Bosses===
Shikigami Bosses are available to all nearby players in the local server. A boss can only be challenged within 30 minutes of being discovered before it escapes.

There are two types of rewards Shikigami Bosses: Gold and Victory. Gold rewards depend on the damage dealt to the boss and is capped at 20k. Victory rewards are given if the boss is defeated in time and at least 10k DMG is dealt, players who discover bosses receive extra shikigami shards for victory rewards. All rewards are sent via in-game mail.

